WE DIDN'T KNOW
THIS WAS YOUR TRAIN--

144
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:17,417
- DON'T TALK OVER ME.

145
00:08:17,458 --> 00:08:20,834
- PLEASE, TAKE MERCY ON US.

146
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,709
- STOP GROVELING AS IF THIS
IS THE WORST DAY OF YOUR LIFE.

147
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:25,625
THIS IS A GOOD DAY.

148
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:27,458
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU ALL
THE OPPORTUNITY

149
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,375
TO REHABILITATE YOURSELVES

150
00:08:29,417 --> 00:08:31,375
AND BECOME PRODUCTIVE
MEMBERS OF YOUR NATION.

151
00:08:31,417 --> 00:08:33,709
RIGHT NOW, YOU'RE LOST,

152
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,375
BUT PLEDGE YOUR LOYALTY
TO ME,

153
00:08:35,417 --> 00:08:37,500
AND I'LL GIVE YOU
A NEW PURPOSE IN YOUR LIVES.

154
00:08:37,542 --> 00:08:39,333
OF COURSE,
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO JOIN,

155
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:41,083
YOU COULD ALWAYS STAY
RIGHT HERE.

156
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:42,542
HOPEFULLY SOMEONE SAVES YOU

157
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:44,250
BEFORE THE NEXT TRAIN
SPEEDS THROUGH,

158
00:08:44,291 --> 00:08:46,250
BUT I WOULDN'T COUNT ON IT.

159
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,250
- NO, WE'LL JOIN.

160
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:48,709
DON'T LEAVE US HERE.

161
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:52,417
- WE PLEDGE OUR LOYALTY TO YOU,
GREAT UNITER.

162
00:08:56,709 --> 00:08:59,750
[jaunty music playing]

163
00:08:59,792 --> 00:09:05,750
♪ ♪

164
00:09:05,792 --> 00:09:07,250
- I DON'T KNOW WHY WE'RE
LEAVING SO EARLY

165
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:09,125
